<class module="orion" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="com.tridium.orion.BIMappable" name="BIMappable" packageName="com.tridium.orion" public="true" interface="true" abstract="true" category="interface">
<description>
The BIMappable interface allows BOrionObjects to create themselves from a&#xa; BObject.  This works as follows.&lt;p/&gt;&#xa; &lt;ol&gt;&#xa;  &lt;li&gt;Register your BOrionObject as an agent on the BObject type that it wants&#xa;      to be able to map.  A BObject can only have one BIMappable orion object&#xa;      registered as an agent on it.  An exception will be thrown if more than&#xa;      one is registered.&lt;/li&gt;&#xa; &#xa; &lt;li&gt;Make sure your BOrionObject implements the BIMappable interface.&lt;/li&gt;&#xa; &lt;/ol&gt;&#xa; &lt;p/&gt;&#xa; &#xa; The OrionSession interface defines &lt;code&gt;mapped&amp;lt;Op&amp;gt;(BObject)&lt;/code&gt; methods&#xa; that give you standard CRUD capabilities. When you use one of these mapped&#xa; methods, Orion will create a BOrionObject based on the registered agent you&#xa; set up.  It will then call the mapFrom(BObject) callback on the orion &#xa; object.
</description>
